            <updated>2019-03-11T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
            <content type="html">
                &lt;p&gt;This article offers a sample of basic Markdown syntax that can be used in Hugo content files, also it shows whether basic HTML elements are decorated with CSS in a Hugo theme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;gblog-post__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;
    &lt;h2 id=&#34;headings&#34;&gt;
        Headings
        &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://martsmusings.uk/post/markdown-syntax/#headings&#34; class=&#34;gblog-post__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor Headings&#34; href=&#34;#headings&#34;&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;gblog-icon gblog_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gblog_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
        &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following HTML &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;h1&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;—&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; elements represent six levels of section headings. &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;h1&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; is the highest section level while &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;h6&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; is the lowest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;gblog-post__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;
    &lt;h1 id=&#34;h1&#34;&gt;
        H1
        &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://martsmusings.uk/post/markdown-syntax/#h1&#34; class=&#34;gblog-post__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor H1&#34; href=&#34;#h1&#34;&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;gblog-icon gblog_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gblog_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
        &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
